name: about
description: The subject matter of the content.
descriptionZh: 事物的关于信息

name: acceptedAnswer
description: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.
descriptionZh: 被接受的最佳答案，通常是出现在问答网站上。不同的网站选择的机制不同，例如社区观点、提问者的观点。

name: acceptedOffer
description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.
descriptionZh: 报价，例如订单中包含的产品、数量、价格的组合

name: acceptedPaymentMethod
description: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.
descriptionZh: 卖家接受的支付方式，现金、信用卡等。

name: acceptsReservations
description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings Yes or No.
descriptionZh: 表示食品相关的企业是否接受预订，值可以是布尔型或者URL。

name: accessCode
description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).
descriptionZh: 密码。或者个人识别码（英语：Personal identification number，缩写为 PIN），又译为用户个人识别号码，常被称为PIN码（PIN number），是一串数字构成的通行码，用来认证使用者身份，授权他进入系统。或者访问某个系统所需要的认证码。

name: accessMode
description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.
descriptionZh: 人类感知外部信息的一种方式，例如：听觉，触觉，文字，视觉，颜色相关，图表，化学视觉，图表视觉，数学公式视觉，音乐视觉。

name: accessModeSufficient
description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.
descriptionZh: 用于全面感知一个资源的所有感知形式的列表

name: accessibilityAPI
description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
descriptionZh: 用于支持系统达成无障碍环境的API

name: accessibilityControl
nameZh: 无障碍环境服务控制方法
description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
descriptionZh: 用于支持系统达成无障碍环境的输入方法

name: accessibilityFeature
nameZh: 无障碍环境服务内容特性
description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
descriptionZh: 用于支持系统达成无障碍环境的输出形式，例如可访问媒体

name: accessibilityHazard
nameZh: 无障碍环境服务的连带风险
description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
descriptionZh: 系统可能对使用者产生生理危害

name: accessibilitySummary
nameZh: 无障碍环境服务的总结
description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."
descriptionZh: 达成无障碍环境可能遇到的风险的摘要描述，例如“提供了简短的描述，但非视觉用户将需要较长的描述”或“提供了简短描述，也不需要更长的描述“。

name: accountId
description: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.
descriptionZh: 账户的编号，例如银行账号，软件系统登陆账号。

name: accountablePerson
description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: 对CreativeWork负有法律责任的特定的人。

name: acquiredFrom
description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.
descriptionZh: 产品获取的机构来源

name: actionAccessibilityRequirement
description: A set of requirements that a must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specied, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

name: actionApplication
description: An application that can complete the request.
descriptionZh: 可以完成该请求的应用程序。

name: actionOption
description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.
descriptionZh: 对象的子属性，受此操作约束的选项。

name: actionPlatform
description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.
descriptionZh: 对给定URL执行操作的高级平台（要指定特定的应用程序或操作系统实例需使用actionApplication）

name: actionStatus
description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.
descriptionZh: 表示当前执行操作的状态

name: actor
description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
descriptionZh: 电视、广播、电影、视频游戏或事件中的演员， 演员既可以与单个项目关联，又可以与一系列剧集、情节相关联。

name: actors
description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
descriptionZh: 演员的复数形式

name: addOn
description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).
descriptionZh: 购买商品的附带赠品。

name: additionalName
description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.
descriptionZh: 人（Person）的别名，可用作中间名字。

name: additionalNumberOfGuests
description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.
descriptionZh: 被邀请人之外，确认参加活动的客人

name: additionalProperty
description:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.



Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.
descriptionZh: 表示实体附加特征的属性值对（例如schema.org中没有匹配属性的产品功能或其他特性）

name: additionalType
description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
descriptionZh: 该项的一个附加类型， 通常用于从外部词典中向微数据语法添加更加具体的类型。它表示事物和事物本身所属的类之间的关系。在RDFa语法中, 对多类型最好使用‘typeof’属性这样的本地RDFa语法. Schema.org 工具对额外类型的理解较弱，特别是外部定义的额外类型。

name: address
description: Physical address of the item.
descriptionZh: 该项的物理地址。

name: addressCountry
description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
descriptionZh: 地址所属国家,比如USA，China

name: addressLocality
description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.
descriptionZh: 地址所在特定区域.如 中关村

name: addressRegion
description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level Administrative division
descriptionZh: 地址中提及的省级地区（例如加州，河南省）

name: advanceBookingRequirement
description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.
descriptionZh: 预定资源需要提前的时间数（例如预定火车票需在发车前至少一小时）

name: affiliation
description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.
descriptionZh: 人所属的组织（例如学校/大学，俱乐部或团队）

name: afterMedia
description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.
descriptionZh: 执行操作前显示的图片或视频等媒体对象

name: agent
description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.
descriptionZh: 发起作用（或产生某种结果）的人或物

name: aggregateRating
description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
descriptionZh: 基于该项的一系列评论的总体评价。

name: aircraft
description: The kind of aircraft (e.g., "Boeing 747").
descriptionZh: 任何可以飞行的载具

name: album
description: A music album.
descriptionZh: 将一定数量以上的歌曲或乐曲集结在一起，并对外发行的一种媒体类型

name: albumProductionType
description: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.
descriptionZh: 专辑的内容分类，例如：音轨，现场专辑，演播室专辑等

name: albumRelease
description: A release of this album.
descriptionZh: 专辑的发行版本，通常具有不同的出版号。例如，某专辑在香港，日本各有一个发行版本。

name: albumReleaseType
description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.
descriptionZh: 专辑的发行版本的类型，例如：单张，EP或专辑。

name: albums
description: A collection of music albums.
descriptionZh: 音乐专辑大全（拼写的单数形式，album）。

name: alignmentType
description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationalLevel'.
descriptionZh: 学习资源与框架节点之间的一种对齐形式。 推荐值包括：“评估”，“教学”，“需要”，“文本复合”，“阅读层”，“教育主体”和“教育层”。

name: alternateName
description: An alias for the item.
descriptionZh: 该项的别名。

name: alternativeHeadline
description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork的副标题。

name: alumni
description: Alumni of an organization.
descriptionZh: 同属于一个组织的人（例如校友）

name: alumniOf
description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.
descriptionZh: 此人的母校。

name: amenityFeature
description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.
descriptionZh: 住宿的便利设施（例如特色或服务）。这个通用财产并没有说明该功能是否包含在主要住宿的报价中，或者是额外的费用。

name: amount
description: The amount of money.
descriptionZh: 金钱的总量

name: amountOfThisGood
description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.
descriptionZh: 订单里货物的总量

name: annualPercentageRate
description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.
descriptionZh: 借款（或投资产生的）年度利率，以单一百分比数表示，表示贷款期间实际的年度资金成本。这包括与交易相关的任何费用或额外费用。

name: answerCount
description: The number of answers this question has received.
descriptionZh: 问题的回复总数

name: application
description: An application that can complete the request.
descriptionZh: 能完成请求的应用软件。

name: applicationCategory
description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.
descriptionZh: 应用软件类型，如“游戏， 多媒体”。

name: applicationSubCategory
description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.
descriptionZh: 应用的子类型，如“街机游戏”。

name: applicationSuite
description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).
descriptionZh: 应用所属的应用套件名称（如，Excel属于Office）。

name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.
descriptionZh: 适用于交货费用或支付费用规范的交付方式。

name: appliesToPaymentMethod
description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.
descriptionZh: 适用于支付费用规范的支付方式。

name: area
description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.
descriptionZh: 广播覆盖的区域。

name: areaServed
description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.
descriptionZh: 服务或产品所覆盖的区域。

name: arrivalAirport
description: The airport where the flight terminates.
descriptionZh: 该航班的终点机场。

name: arrivalBusStop
description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.
descriptionZh: 公交车到达的车站

name: arrivalGate
description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.
descriptionZh: 航班到达的登机口

name: arrivalPlatform
description: The platform where the train arrives.
descriptionZh: 火车到达的站台

name: arrivalStation
description: The station where the train trip ends.
descriptionZh: 火车旅程结束的车站。

name: arrivalTerminal
description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.
descriptionZh: 航班到达的航站楼。

name: arrivalTime
description: The expected arrival time.
descriptionZh: （理想）达到时间

name: artEdition
description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").
descriptionZh: 一个出版物的某一版本印发的拷贝数目

name: artMedium
description: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)
descriptionZh: 使用的材料。（例如油，水彩，亚克力，大理石，数字，平版印刷，凹版，粉彩，木刻，铅笔，混合媒体等）。

name: artform
description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.
descriptionZh: 艺术的形式，例如油画、素描、雕塑、打印、照片、组合、拼贴等。

name: articleBody
description: The actual body of the article.
descriptionZh: 文章的主体部分。

name: articleSection
description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.
descriptionZh: 在杂志或报纸中文章可能属于一个或多个‘章节’, 比如体育章节, 生活章节, 等等。

name: artworkSurface
description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.
descriptionZh: 艺术品的辅助材料，例如 帆布，纸，木材，板木等。

name: assembly
description: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.
descriptionZh: 编译过的程序库文件，如mscorlib.dll system.web.dll

name: assemblyVersion
description: Associated product/technology version. e.g., .NET Framework 4.5.
descriptionZh: 相关的程序库的版本，比如.NET Framework 4.5

name: associatedArticle
description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.
descriptionZh: 与该媒体对象相关的新闻文章。

name: associatedMedia
description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.
descriptionZh: 对该创作作品编码的媒体对象。此属性是编码的一个代名词。

name: athlete
description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.
descriptionZh: 作为运动队队员的人，球员（与教练相对）

name: attendee
description: A person or organization attending the event.
descriptionZh: 出席某一活动的组织或个人。

name: attendees
description: A person attending the event.
descriptionZh: 出席某一活动的组织或个人。 (拼写单数形式，attendee)。

name: audience
description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.
descriptionZh: 该作品所面向的观众，也就是该作品为哪些群体创作。

name: audienceType
description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).
descriptionZh: 与给定受众相关的目标群体。

name: audio
description: An embedded audio object.
descriptionZh: 嵌入式音频对象。

name: authenticator
description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

name: author
description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.
descriptionZh: 此内容或评分的作者。

name: availability
description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.
descriptionZh: 比如有现货，无现货，需要预定 等

name: availabilityEnds
description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.
descriptionZh: 此报价中物品或服务的下架，下市时间

name: availabilityStarts
description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.
descriptionZh: 此报价中物品或服务的上架、上市时间

name: availableAtOrFrom
description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).
descriptionZh: 可以获得此报价的地方（比如说商店位置）

name: availableChannel
description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).
descriptionZh: 访问服务的方式（例如，电话银行，网站，位置等）

name: availableDeliveryMethod
description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.
descriptionZh: 报价所支持的物流递送方式，例如当日到达，隔日到达，邮局包裹等

name: availableFrom
description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.
descriptionZh: 可以从商店、储物柜等地方提货的开始时间

name: availableLanguage
description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage
descriptionZh: 该商品所支持的语言

name: availableOnDevice
description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.
descriptionZh: 运行该应用程序所需要的设备，用于运行应用程序需要特定品牌或型号的情况。

name: availableThrough
description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.
descriptionZh: 过了该日期，该商品将不可取件。

name: award
description: An award won by or for this item.
descriptionZh: 此人或该创作性作品获得的奖金(奖项)。

name: awards
description: Awards won by or for this item.
descriptionZh: 此人或该创作性作品获得的奖金(奖项)。(拼写的单数形式, award)。

name: awayTeam
description: The away team in a sports event.
descriptionZh: 体育赛事中的客场队。

name: baseSalary
description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.
descriptionZh: 该职位的基本工资。

name: bccRecipient
description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.
descriptionZh: 消息的密送收信人，这些人的名字不会被其他收信人看到

name: bed
description: The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.
descriptionZh: 住宿的床型，例如大床，单人床

name: beforeMedia
description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.
descriptionZh: 执行操作后显示的图片或视频等媒体对象

name: benefits
description: Description of benefits associated with the job.
descriptionZh: 与该工作相关的福利。

name: bestRating
description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.
descriptionZh: 该评分系统中允许的最高评分分数，如果没有设置最高评分分数，就假定为5。

name: billingAddress
description: The billing address for the order.
descriptionZh: 账单的邮寄地址。

name: billingIncrement
description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.
descriptionZh: 指定了作为账单计费基础的最小数量和舍入增量。测量单位由unitCode属性指定。

name: billingPeriod
description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.
descriptionZh: 单据结算的时间间隔。

name: birthDate
description: Date of birth.
descriptionZh: 出生的日期。

name: birthPlace
description: The place where the person was born.
descriptionZh: 此人出生的地方。

name: bitrate
description: The bitrate of the media object.
descriptionZh: 媒体对象的比特率。

name: blogPost
description: A posting that is part of this blog.
descriptionZh: 该博客的帖子之一。

name: blogPosts
description: The postings that are part of this blog.
descriptionZh: 该博客的帖子(拼写的单数形式, blogPost)。

name: boardingGroup
description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.
descriptionZh: 航空公司的登机顺序或优先顺序。

name: boardingPolicy
description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).
descriptionZh: 航空公司所用的登机政策的类型（例如基于区域的、基于分组的）。

name: bookEdition
description: The edition of the book.
descriptionZh: 该书的版本。

name: bookFormat
description: The format of the book.
descriptionZh: 该书的样式。

name: bookingAgent
description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.
descriptionZh: 票务服务的订票代理商

name: bookingTime
description: The date and time the reservation was booked.
descriptionZh: 预订的日期和时间。

name: borrower
description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.
descriptionZh: 参与者属性的子属性。借入东西的人。

name: box
description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.
descriptionZh: 边界框是由两个点形成的矩形所包围的区域。第一个点是下角，第二个点是上角。边界框用空格符分隔的两个点来表示。

name: branchCode
description:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.



For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.
descriptionZh: 一个简短的文本编码（也称为商店码）， 用于唯一标示商务地点。

name: branchOf
description: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical)branch.
descriptionZh: 如果有的话，就是指该本地企业所属的更大的机构。

name: brand
description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.
descriptionZh: 与该产品或服务相关的品牌，或者是由该组织或个人维护的品牌。

name: breadcrumb
description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.
descriptionZh: 网页内元素，说明当前页面在网站中所属的层次结构

name: broadcastAffiliateOf
description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.
descriptionZh: 广播网络的内容来自的站点

name: broadcastChannelId
description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.
descriptionZh: 可以在供应商中识别出该BroadcastService的唯一地址。 在美国，这通常是一个数字。

name: broadcastDisplayName
description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.
descriptionZh: 频道指南中显示的名称。 对于许多美国偶来说，就是网络名称。

name: broadcastFrequency
description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequences of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

name: broadcastFrequencyValue
description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

name: broadcastOfEvent
description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.
descriptionZh: 正在播放的活动，如体育赛事或颁奖仪式。

name: broadcastServiceTier
nameZh: 广播频道所属的服务级别
description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).
descriptionZh: 访问频道所需的服务类型（例如标准版或高级版）。

name: broadcastTimezone
description: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts
descriptionZh: 广播服务所在的时区

name: broadcaster
description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.
descriptionZh: 拥有或经营广播服务的组织。

name: broker
description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.
descriptionZh: 安排买方和卖方进行交易的实体。 大多数情况下，经纪人从未获取或发布交易所涉及的产品或服务的所有权。

name: browserRequirements
description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.
descriptionZh: 用可读文本指定的对浏览器的要求，如“需要对HTML5的支持”。

name: busName
description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).
descriptionZh: 公共汽车的名称。

name: busNumber
description: The unique identifier for the bus.
descriptionZh: 公共汽车的唯一标识。

name: businessFunction
description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.
descriptionZh: 商业职能，如销售，维修，储藏

name: buyer
description: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.
descriptionZh: 参与者属性的子属性。买东西的参与者、个人或者组织。

name: byArtist
description: The artist that performed this album or recording.
descriptionZh: 参演该专辑或MV的艺术家。

name: calories
description: The number of calories.
descriptionZh: 卡路里含量。

name: candidate
description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.
descriptionZh: 对象的子属性。该动作的候选人。

name: caption
description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the encodingFormat.
descriptionZh: 特指图片和视频的标题

name: carbohydrateContent
description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.
descriptionZh: 含碳水化合物的克数。

name: cargoVolume
description:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.



Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet



Note: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.
descriptionZh: 通常指汽车后备箱的容积

name: carrier
description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.
descriptionZh: 承运商是一个过时的术语，表示包裹运送和航班的“提供者”。

name: carrierRequirements
description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).
descriptionZh: 指定应用程序的特定运营商要求（例如，应用程序可能仅在特定运营商网络上运行）。

name: catalog
description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.
descriptionZh: 包含此数据集的数据目录。

name: catalogNumber
description: The catalog number for the release.
descriptionZh: 发行的目录号。

name: category
description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.
descriptionZh: 该项的类别。

name: ccRecipient
description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.
descriptionZh: 消息的抄送收信人，这些人的名字可以被其他收信人看到

name: character
description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.
descriptionZh: 与该创造性作品有关的虚构人物。

name: characterAttribute
description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).
descriptionZh: 代表虚构角色特定方面（技能、力量、特征点、优势、劣势）的数据。

name: characterName
description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.
descriptionZh: 演出和剧目中演员所扮演的角色的名字

name: cheatCode
description: Cheat codes to the game.
descriptionZh: 游戏中的作弊代码。

name: checkinTime
description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.
descriptionZh: 酒店的最早入住时间

name: checkoutTime
description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.
descriptionZh: 酒店的最晚退房时间

name: childMaxAge
description: Maximal age of the child.
descriptionZh: 满足条件的儿童的最大年龄

name: childMinAge
description: Minimal age of the child.
descriptionZh: 满足条件的儿童的最小年龄

name: children
description: A child of the person.
descriptionZh: 此人的孩子。

name: cholesterolContent
description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.
descriptionZh: 含胆固醇的毫克数。

name: circle
description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.
descriptionZh: 圆是以某个指定经维度为中心指定长度为半径的区域。圆是由一对坐标加上以米为单位的半径来表示的。

name: citation
description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.
descriptionZh: 引用或引用另一个创作作品，如其他出版物，网页，学术文章等。

name: claimReviewed
description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.
descriptionZh: 针对ClaimReview中的某个声明做出的简短评论摘要

name: clipNumber
description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.
descriptionZh: 该剪辑在有序的剪辑组中的位置。

name: closes
description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.
descriptionZh: 地点或服务在一周的某一天的关闭时间。

name: coach
description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.
descriptionZh: 在体育队担任教练角色的人。

name: codeRepository
description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex).
descriptionZh: 源码库链接，如SVN，github，codeplex

name: codeSampleType
description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.
descriptionZh: 什么类型的代码示例：完整的解决方案，代码片段，内联代码，脚本，模板

name: colleague
description: A colleague of the person.
descriptionZh: 此人的同事。

name: colleagues
description: A colleague of the person.
descriptionZh: 此人的同事 (拼写的单数形式, colleague)。

name: collection
description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.
descriptionZh: 一组事物

name: color
description: The color of the product.
descriptionZh: 该产品的颜色。

name: comment
description: Comments, typically from users.
descriptionZh: 评论，一般是用户对CreativeWork的评论。

name: commentCount
description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork（例如文章，问题或答案）收到的评论数量。 这最适用于使用评论系统发布在网站上的作品; 其他地方也可能存在额外的评论。

name: commentText
description: The text of the UserComment.
descriptionZh: UserComment的文本。

name: commentTime
description: The time at which the UserComment was made.
descriptionZh: UserComment撰写的时间。

name: competitor
description: A competitor in a sports event.
descriptionZh: 体育赛事中的竞争对手。

name: composer
description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.
descriptionZh: 写了一首作曲的人或者组织，或者是在一些活动上表演的一部作品的作曲家。

name: confirmationNumber
description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.
descriptionZh: 已经收到的订单或者付款的确认编号。

name: contactOption
description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).
descriptionZh: 该联络点提供的选项（例如免费电话号码或对听力受损呼叫者的支持）。

name: contactPoint
description: A contact point for a person or organization.
descriptionZh: 个人或组织的联络点。

name: contactPoints
description: A contact point for a person or organization.
descriptionZh: 个人或组织的联络点。（拼写的单数形式，contactPoint）。

name: contactType
description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.
descriptionZh: 为了不同的目的，个人或组织可以有不同的接触点。例如，销售联络点，公关联络点等。此属性用于指定联系人的种类。

name: containedIn
description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
descriptionZh: 地点的包含关系

name: containedInPlace
description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
descriptionZh: 地点的包含关系

name: containsPlace
description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.
descriptionZh: 地点的包含关系

name: containsSeason
description: A season that is part of the media series.
descriptionZh: 该媒体系列包含的季

name: contentLocation
description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.
descriptionZh: 内容的位置。

name: contentRating
description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.
descriptionZh: 一项内容的官方评级，如‘MPAA PG-13’。

name: contentSize
description: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.
descriptionZh: 文件大小（MB或KB）。

name: contentType
description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.
descriptionZh: 支持的EntryPoint响应的内容类型。

name: contentUrl
description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.
descriptionZh: 指向媒体对象（如图像文件或视频文件）的实际编码字节流

name: contributor
description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork协助者/次级贡献者。

name: cookTime
description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in ISO 8601 duration format.
descriptionZh: 烹该菜实际所用的时间，使用ISO 8601时长格式。

name: cookingMethod
description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...
descriptionZh: 烹调方法，如油炸、蒸等。

name: copyrightHolder
description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork合法版权的拥有者。

name: copyrightYear
description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork版权授权生效的年份。

name: countriesNotSupported
description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
descriptionZh: 应用不支持的国家。你也可以提供两个字母的ISO 3166-1 α-2国家代码。

name: countriesSupported
description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
descriptionZh: 应用支持的国家。你也可以提供两个字母的ISO 3166-1 α-2国家代码。

name: countryOfOrigin
description: The country of the principal offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie or program.
descriptionZh: 对电影或节目负责的生产公司或个人的办事处所在的国家。

name: course
description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.
descriptionZh: 事物所处的位置，这类事物的位置不是一个点，而是一条路线

name: courseCode
description: The identifier for the Course used by the course provider (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).
descriptionZh: 课程提供者使用的课程的标识符（例如CS101或6.001）。

name: courseMode
description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).
descriptionZh: 课程的传播方式或媒介，或者是学习的模式。值可以是文本标签，例如在线、现场、混合、同步、异步、兼职，也可以是来自受控词表的术语的URL引用。

name: coursePrerequisites
description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another Course or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using AlignmentObject.
descriptionZh: 参加课程的要求。可以是完成另一门课程或者像“老师的许可”之类的文本描述。

name: coverageEndTime
description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.
descriptionZh: 博客对一个事件的报导结束时间

name: coverageStartTime
description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.
descriptionZh: 博客对一个事件的报导开始时间

name: creator
description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: 该 CreativeWork 的创作者/作者。跟CreativeWork的Author属性一样。

name: creditedTo
description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.
descriptionZh: 一个作品除主要作者外的其他贡献者，例如 “Red and Blue”那首歌的贡献者是“Stefani Germanotta乐队”，但是主唱是Lady Gaga。

name: cssSelector
description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a SpeakableSpecification or WebPageElement. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

name: currenciesAccepted
description:
The currency accepted.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".
descriptionZh: 接收的货币，使用ISO 4217货币格式。

name: currency
description:
The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".
descriptionZh: 与amount一起使用，说明金额对应的币种，例如美元，人民币，使用3个字母的 ISO 4217 格式

name: customer
description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.
descriptionZh: 下单或支付单据的一方。

name: dataFeedElement
description: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.
descriptionZh: 数据源通常发布多条数据，其中的数据用此属性标记

name: dataset
description: A dataset contained in this catalog.
descriptionZh: 该目录中包含的数据集。

name: datasetTimeInterval
description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).
descriptionZh: 数据集的时间适用范围，例如 2011年人口普查数据集，2011年（按ISO 8601时间间隔格式）。

name: dateCreated
description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.
descriptionZh: 创作出CreativeWork的日期。

name: dateDeleted
description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.
descriptionZh: 该项从DataFeed中删除的日期时间。

name: dateIssued
description: The date the ticket was issued.
descriptionZh: 该票发布的日期。

name: dateModified
description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.
descriptionZh: CreativeWork最近被修改过的日期。

name: datePosted
description: Publication date for the job posting.
descriptionZh: 职位广告发布的日期。

name: datePublished
description: Date of first broadcast/publication.
descriptionZh: 首次广播/出版的日期。

name: dateRead
description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.
descriptionZh: 如果存在单个的收件人，就是消息被收件人读取的日期/时间。

name: dateReceived
description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.
descriptionZh: 如果存在单个的收件人，就是消息被收件人接收的日期/时间。

name: dateSent
description: The date/time at which the message was sent.
descriptionZh: 消息被发送的日期/时间。

name: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.
descriptionZh: 车辆首次在有关公共当局登记的日期。

name: dateline
description:
A dateline is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.



Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using locationCreated (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written). For location depicted or described in the content, use contentLocation.



Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".
descriptionZh: 发稿信息是包含在新闻文章中的一小段短文，用于描述新闻的事件，地点，概要描述，但通常省略日期。

name: dayOfWeek
description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.
descriptionZh: 一周中有效营业的天数

name: deathDate
description: Date of death.
descriptionZh: 死亡日期。

name: deathPlace
description: The place where the person died.
descriptionZh: 该人死亡的地方

name: defaultValue
description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.
descriptionZh: 输入的默认值。 对于期望文字的属性，默认值为文字值，对于期望对象的属性，它是对当前值之一的ID引用。

name: deliveryAddress
description: Destination address.
descriptionZh: 目的地址。

name: deliveryLeadTime
description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.
descriptionZh: 就是指收到订单和货物离开仓库或准备取件（如果是上门取货的话）之间的延迟。

name: deliveryMethod
description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.
descriptionZh: instrument的子属性。物流送货的方式。

name: deliveryStatus
description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).
descriptionZh: 物流中，每一个递送环节形成一个送货状态记录。

name: department
description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.
descriptionZh: 组织与该组织某个部门之间的关系，也被描述成组织（允许不同的网址，标识，开放时间）。 例如：一家有药店的商店，或者是一间带咖啡厅的面包店。

name: departureAirport
description: The airport where the flight originates.
descriptionZh: 飞机起飞的机场。

name: departureBusStop
description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.
descriptionZh: 汽车出发的公交站或车站。

name: departureGate
description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.
descriptionZh: 飞行出发门的标识。

name: departurePlatform
description: The platform from which the train departs.
descriptionZh: 火车出发的站台。

name: departureStation
description: The station from which the train departs.
descriptionZh: 火车出发的火车站。

name: departureTerminal
description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.
descriptionZh: 飞机出发的航站楼的标识。

name: departureTime
description: The expected departure time.
descriptionZh: 预计的出发时间。

name: dependencies
description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.
descriptionZh: 完成文章中的步骤所需的先决条件。

name: depth
description: The depth of the item.
descriptionZh: 该项的深度。

name: description
description: A description of the item.
descriptionZh: 该项的一个简单描述。

name: device
description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.
descriptionZh: 运行应用所需的设备。运行该应用所要求的设备具体到品牌/型号时，用到此属性。

name: director
description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
descriptionZh: 电影、电视剧、电视剧集或电视游戏的导演。

name: directors
description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
descriptionZh: 电影、电视剧、电视剧集或电视游戏的导演。

name: disambiguatingDescription
description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.
descriptionZh: 描述的子属性。 用于消除与其他类似项之间歧义的简短描述。 其它属性（特别是名称）的信息对于消歧义可能是必要的。

name: discount
description: Any discount applied (to an Order).
descriptionZh: 任何适用（于订单）的折扣。

name: discountCode
description: Code used to redeem a discount.
descriptionZh: 用来兑换折扣的代码。

name: discountCurrency
description:
The currency of the discount.



Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".
descriptionZh: 折扣所使用的货币类型。

name: discusses
description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.
descriptionZh: 与UserComment相关的CreativeWork。

name: discussionUrl
description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: 到包含CreativeWork评论页面的链接。

name: dissolutionDate
description: The date that this organization was dissolved.
descriptionZh: 该组织解散的日期。

name: distance
description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.
descriptionZh: 行程的距离，例如行驶或旅行。

name: distribution
description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.
descriptionZh: 该数据集的可下载形式，在特定位置，以特定格式。

name: doorTime
description: The time admission will commence.
descriptionZh: 活动时，开门允许观众入场的时间

name: downloadUrl
description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.
descriptionZh: 它表示当文件可下载时，用于下载该二进制形式文件的URL。

name: downvoteCount
description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.
descriptionZh: 来自该社区的，对于这个问题、答案或意见的反对数量。

name: driveWheelConfiguration
description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.
descriptionZh: 驱动轮构造，即哪个风轮将经由动力传动系统从车辆的发动机接收扭矩。

name: dropoffLocation
description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.
descriptionZh: 可以归还租车的地方。

name: dropoffTime
description: When a rental car can be dropped off.
descriptionZh: 可以归还租车的时间。

name: duns
description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.
descriptionZh: 用于识别组织机构或商务人士的邓氏编码。

name: duration
description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.
descriptionZh: 该项的时长（电影， 录音, 事件, 等等），时长格式见 ISO 8601 date format。

name: durationOfWarranty
description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.
descriptionZh: 保修期限。一般的单位代码是ANN表示年数，MON表示月数，DAY表示天数。

name: duringMedia
description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.
descriptionZh: 执行操作时显示的图片或视频等媒体对象

name: editor
description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: 指定编辑CreativeWork的人。

name: educationalAlignment
description: An alignment to an established educational framework.
descriptionZh: 与已建立的教育框架相一致。

name: educationalCredentialAwarded
description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

name: educationalFramework
description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.
descriptionZh: 教育资源所对应的教学标准。

name: educationalRole
description: An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.
descriptionZh: 受教育观众在教育活动中所处的角色。

name: educationalUse
description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.
descriptionZh: 教育资源预期的用途，例如家庭作业，小组项目。

name: elevation
description: The elevation of a location (WGS 84). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNITOFMEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.
descriptionZh: 该地的高程。

name: eligibleCustomerType
description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.
descriptionZh: 哪些顾客适用于这个报价，例如促销折扣仅适用于60岁以上客户。

name: eligibleDuration
description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.
descriptionZh: 报价的有效时间，例如促销折扣仅限于某一周有效。

name: eligibleQuantity
description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.
descriptionZh: 报价最多可有购买多少货品，例如每客户最多可以购买一个优惠产品。

name: eligibleRegion
description:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.



See also ineligibleRegion.
descriptionZh: 报价适用的区域，例如免运费仅限于北京三环内用户。

name: eligibleTransactionVolume
description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.
descriptionZh: 适用适用的最低消费，例如满100免运费。

name: email
description: Email address.
descriptionZh: 邮箱地址。

name: embedUrl
description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.
descriptionZh: 指向特定格式视频播放器的URL。一般来说，这种信息在嵌入式标签的src元素中，它应该跟loc标签的内容不一样。

name: employee
description: Someone working for this organization.
descriptionZh: 一位该组织的雇员。

name: employees
description: People working for this organization.
descriptionZh: 该组织的雇员。 (拼写的单数形式, employee)

name: employmentType
description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).
descriptionZh: 就业类型（例如全职，兼职，合同，临时，季节性，实习）。

name: encodesCreativeWork
description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.
descriptionZh: 该媒体对象编码的CreativeWork。

name: encoding
description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.
descriptionZh: 一个对CreativeWork编码的媒体对象。

name: encodingFormat
description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).



In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.



Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.
descriptionZh: 编码格式，如mp3, mpeg4, 等等。

name: encodingType
description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.
descriptionZh: 支持的EntryPoint请求的编码类型。

name: encodings
description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.
descriptionZh: 对CreativeWork编码的媒体对象。(拼写的单数形式, encoding)

name: endDate
description: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).
descriptionZh: 活动（事件）结束时间。

name: endTime
description:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.



Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.
descriptionZh: 事件的结束时间

name: endorsee
description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.
descriptionZh: 参与者的子属性。 被支持的人/组织。

name: entertainmentBusiness
description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.
descriptionZh: location的子属性。该行为发生于的娱乐行业。

name: episode
description: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.
descriptionZh: 电视剧或其某一季的剧集。

name: episodeNumber
description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.
descriptionZh: 电视剧或其某一季的剧集号。

name: episodes
description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.
descriptionZh: 电视剧或其某一季的剧集。(拼写的单数形式, episode)

name: equal
description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.
descriptionZh: 数值之间的排序关系，表示主语等于谓语。

name: error
description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.
descriptionZh: 对于失败的操作，有关故障原因的更多信息。

name: estimatedCost
description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.
descriptionZh: 执行操作的物料成本估价

name: estimatedFlightDuration
description: The estimated time the flight will take.
descriptionZh: 预计的飞行时间。

name: estimatedSalary
description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

name: event
description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
descriptionZh: 即将发生或已经过去且与这个地方或机构相关的事件。

name: eventStatus
description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.
descriptionZh: 表示事件的状态，事件被取消或重新安排时特别有用。

name: events
description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.
descriptionZh: 即将发生或已经过去且与这个地方或机构相关的事件。 (拼写的单数形式，如event)

name: exampleOfWork
description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.
descriptionZh: 相关的创作，通常二者有范例，参考的关系。

name: executableLibraryName
description: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.
descriptionZh: 软件开发中，软件库的文件名，例如windows 里的DLL文件。

name: exerciseCourse
description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.
descriptionZh: 活动的执行场地。

name: exifData
description: exif data for this object.
descriptionZh: 该对象的EXIF数据。

name: expectedArrivalFrom
description: The earliest date the package may arrive.
descriptionZh: 包裹可能到达的最早日期。

name: expectedArrivalUntil
description: The latest date the package may arrive.
descriptionZh: 包裹可能到达的最晚日期。

name: expectsAcceptanceOf
nameZh: 行动前必须接受的条件
description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.
descriptionZh: 行动前必须接受的条件。例如，用户可能需要购买电影才能观看。

name: experienceRequirements
nickname: 工作经验要求，职位要求
description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.
descriptionZh: 职位所需的技能和经验的描述。

name: expires
description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.
descriptionZh: 内容过期日期，不再有用或可用。 适用于影片。

name: familyName
description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.
descriptionZh: 姓。 在美国，是一个人姓名中的最后一个字。

name: fatContent
description: The number of grams of fat.
descriptionZh: 脂肪的克数。

name: faxNumber
description: The fax number.
descriptionZh: 传真号。

name: featureList
description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).
descriptionZh: 应用程序提供的功能或模块。

name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.
descriptionZh: 金融产品或金融服务机构适用的费用，佣金和其他条款的说明。

name: fiberContent
description: The number of grams of fiber.
descriptionZh: 纤维的克数。

name: fileFormat
description: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.
descriptionZh: 文件格式（或文件类型）是指电脑为了存储信息而使用的对信息的特殊编码方式，是用于识别内部储存的资料。比如有的储存图片，有的储存程序，有的储存文字信息。每一类信息，都可以一种或多种文件格式保存在电脑存储中。每一种文件格式通常会有一种或多种扩展名可以用来识别，但也可能没有扩展名。扩展名可以帮助应用程序识别的文件格式。

name: fileSize
description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.
descriptionZh: 文件大小能衡量一个计算机文件的大小。通常情况下以带前缀的字节数表示。

name: firstPerformance
description: The date and place the work was first performed.
descriptionZh: 首演的日期和地点。

name: flightDistance
description: The distance of the flight.
descriptionZh: 航班飞行的距离。

name: flightNumber
description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.
descriptionZh: 包含国际航空运输协会（IATA）代码在内的航班唯一标记号。例如，联合航空公司对应的IATA代码是“UA”，它有一架航班为110，那么它的航班号是“UA110”。

name: floorSize
description: The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard
descriptionZh: 房间大小。常用单位代码：MTK表示平方米，FTK表示平方英尺，YDK表示平方码

name: followee
description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.
descriptionZh: 社交网络上被别人关注

name: follows
description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.
descriptionZh: 社交网络上主动关注其他人或组织

name: foodEstablishment
description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.
descriptionZh: 餐饮场所

name: foodEvent
description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.
descriptionZh: 位置的子属性，食物事件发生的地点

name: founder
description: A person who founded this organization.
descriptionZh: 组织机构的创始人

name: founders
description: A person who founded this organization.
descriptionZh: 组织机构的创始人

name: foundingDate
description: The date that this organization was founded.
descriptionZh: 组织机构成立的日期

name: foundingLocation
description: The place where the Organization was founded.
descriptionZh: 组织机构成立的地点

name: free
description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.
descriptionZh: 用于表示可以免费获取该出版物或事件的标志。

name: fromLocation
description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.
descriptionZh: 发源地

name: fuelConsumption
description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).



  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.
descriptionZh: 车辆行驶特定距离或时间所消耗的燃料量（例如每100公里升）

name: fuelEfficiency
description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).



  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.
descriptionZh: 每单位燃料行驶的距离

name: fuelType
description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.
descriptionZh: 适用于发动机或发动机的燃料类型。 如果车辆只有一个发动机，该属性可以直接连接到车辆。

name: funder
description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.
descriptionZh: 通过某种财务贡献支持（赞助）某事的个人或组织。

name: game
description: Video game which is played on this server.
descriptionZh: 服务器上运行的游戏

name: gameItem
description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.
descriptionZh: 游戏中存在的物品

name: gameLocation
description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).
descriptionZh: 游戏中的真实或虚拟的地址

name: gamePlatform
description: The electronic systems used to play video games.
descriptionZh: 用于玩电子游戏的电子系统。

name: gameServer
description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.
descriptionZh: 支持游戏运行的服务器

name: gameTip
description: Links to tips, tactics, etc.
descriptionZh: 游戏攻略指的就是指官方或非官方发布的，可以为玩家提供一些游戏经验与心得的文字或视频类的教材。引导玩家特别是新手玩家熟悉并能尽快的对相关游戏的更多深入了解的文章，或者也可以说是一些玩家自己的游戏心得，跟大家一起分享。有些玩家也会称之为游戏秘籍。

name: gender
description: Gender of the person. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender.
descriptionZh: 人的性别

name: genre
description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.
descriptionZh: （文学、艺术、电影或音乐的）体裁，类型

name: geo
description: The geo coordinates of the place.
descriptionZh: 地理位置的坐标。

name: geoContains
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoCoveredBy
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoCovers
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoCrosses
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoDisjoint
description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

name: geoEquals
description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

name: geoIntersects
description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoMidpoint
description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.
descriptionZh: 中心点的经纬度

name: geoOverlaps
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geoRadius
description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).
descriptionZh: 区域半径

name: geoTouches
description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

name: geoWithin
description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

name: geographicArea
description: The geographic area associated with the audience.
descriptionZh: 受众群所在地理区域

name: givenName
description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.
descriptionZh: 名。在美国，是一个人名字中的第一个字

name: globalLocationNumber
description: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
descriptionZh: 全球位置码

name: grantee
description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.
descriptionZh: 获得此许可的人员，组织，联络人或受众。

name: greater
description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.
descriptionZh: 数学中的大于

name: greaterOrEqual
description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.
descriptionZh: 数学中的大于等于

name: gtin12

descriptionZh: 12位全球贸易品项识别码

name: gtin13

descriptionZh: 13位全球贸易品项识别码

name: gtin14
description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
descriptionZh: 14位全球贸易品项识别码

name: gtin8

name: hasMenu

name: hasMenuItem

descriptionZh: 食物或饮料菜单或菜单条中包含的内容

name: hasMenuSection

descriptionZh: 为组织、个人或服务提供的清单列表

descriptionZh: 表示某个作品是该作品的一部分

name: headline
description: Headline of the article.
descriptionZh: 文章标题

name: height
description: The height of the item.
descriptionZh: 高度

name: highPrice
description:

description:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.



  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

name: price
description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.



Usage guidelines:



  • Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
descriptionZh: 附加到价格规范及其子类型时的产品或价格组件的报价。使用指南：使用priceCurrency属性（使用ISO 4217代码，例如“USD”），而不是在值中包含不明确的符号，例如“$”。使用 '。' （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。避免使用这些符号作为可读性分隔符。 请注意，RDFa和Microdata语法都允许使用“content =”属性来发布简单的机器可读值，以及更加人性化的格式化。使用0123456789（Unicode'DIGIT ZERO'（U + 0030）到'DIGIT NINE'（U + 0039））的值，而不是表面上类似的Unicode符号。

name: speakable
description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.



The speakable property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:



1.) id-value URL references - uses id-value of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of speakable has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.



2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the cssSelector property.



3.) XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the xpath property.



For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For thiswe define a supporting type, SpeakableSpecification which is defined to be a possible value of the speakable property.

name: temporalCoverage
description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".



Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.
descriptionZh: 作品所描写或有效于的时间段，格式是根据ISO8601的DateTime或者string。数据作品通常会有精确的相关时间（例：2011年国家普查会符合ISO8601被写为“2011/2012”）。其它作品（学术文章，电影，电视剧等）会更广泛地在作品内或利用知名的链接来标明时间段。
